The paper focuses on the security concerns of outsourcing software middleboxes to third-party service providers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficient processing of middleboxes within the highly constrained enclave space, which is related to network architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also addresses the challenges of stateful middlebox processing, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
